hopobject.body: A packet of envelopes theinformedvermonter.com House Majority Leader Eric Cantor, R-Va., and Rep. Bob Goodlatte, R-Va., chairman of the House Judiciary Committee, have been crafting a bill, expected to be called the Kids Act, to offer a path to citizenship only to children who were brought to the U.S. illegally by their parents -- a move critics said would separate families by sending parents home and only addresses a fraction of the 11 million undocumented people living in the United States.
